-- Germany Seeks Pricing Data From Gas-Station Chains, FAZ Says
-- B y   P a t r i c k   D o n a h u e
-- 2012-04-03T17:53:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/germany-seeks-pricing-data-from-gas-station-chains-faz-says.html
Germany ’s Federal Cartel Office is
seeking information from the country’s five largest gas-station
operators following accusations from independent rivals about
their pricing practices,  Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  said.  The government sought data from the operators of BP/Aral,
Esso, Jet, Shell and Total as a first step in any further
investigation, the newspaper cited the cartel office as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patrick Donahue in Berlin at 
